      • convertTypeNodeAST

        @Nullable
public static Node.TypeDeclarationNode convertTypeNodeAST(Node n)
        The root of a JSTypeExpression is very different from an AST node, even though we use the same Java class to represent them. This function converts root nodes of JSTypeExpressions into TypeDeclaration ASTs, to make them more similar to ordinary AST nodes.
        Returns:
        the root node of a TypeDeclaration AST, or null if no type is available for the node.
